ssnap_field

Source: R/internal_fields_72hrs.R
onset_to_clock_start.Rd

ssnap_field is a set of named quosures (code snippets) used to describe calculations to perform on individual records, which will be later used to create performance measures.

onset_to_clock_start

Format

An object of class list of length 1.

Details

Example uses of these fields are to calculate time differences, or to perform complex row calculations such as eligibility for thrombolysis.

We aren't actually creating these extra data rows - instead we calculate the extra information at the same time as doing the summarising: the quosures in the ssnap_measures lists insert these snippets to perform the calculation.

Writing the code in this way allows us to test these code segments individually in the unit tests.
